Review complete. Saved to `NSQ-03_review.md`. Here's the summary:

**5 BUGs, 2 QUESTIONs found. Assessment: FIX FIRST.**

Key findings:

| # | Type | Severity | Lines | Description |
|---|------|----------|-------|-------------|
| 1 | BUG | Medium | 279-280 | `PutMessage` uses `c.RLock()` instead of `c.exitMutex.RLock()` ‚Äî TOCTOU race allows `put()` to a closed backend |
| 2 | BUG | Medium | 309-312 | `PutMessageDeferred` has no `Exiting()` check or `exitMutex` guard at all |
| 3 | BUG | Medium | 537 | `processDeferredQueue` ignores `c.put(msg)` error ‚Äî message already removed from PQ+map, silently lost |
| 4 | BUG | Medium | 574 | `processInFlightQueue` same issue ‚Äî discarded `put()` error loses message |
| 5 | BUG | Low | 239 | `flush()` swallows all write errors, always returns nil |
| 6 | QUESTION | Low | 117-118 | `initPQ()` reassigns maps without `inFlightMutex`/`deferredMutex` |
| 7 | QUESTION | Low | 534-536 | Early `goto exit` on pop failure delays processing of other ready messages |

The most critical pattern is the **inconsistent exit synchronization**: `RequeueMessage` correctly uses `exitMutex.RLock()`, but `PutMessage` and `PutMessageDeferred` do not, creating a race window where messages can be written to a closing/closed channel.
